The Federal Capital Territory (FCT) administration has discharged three patients who were receiving coronavirus treatment in Abuja. FCT minister, Mohammed Bello, broke the news in a post on the Twitter Wednesday night. Bello said the development brings to 23, the total number of patients discharged in the nation’s capital· He tweeted: “Dear FCT residents, I am glad to announce that additional three (3) #COVID19 patients have been discharged from the isolation and treatment centre in the FCT after they tested negative. “The total number of discharged patients in the FCT is now 23 as at 7:30pm, April 15th, 2020.”  Another COVID-19 patient dies of complications in Lagos Death toll hits 10 as NCDC confirms 13 new coronavirus cases FCT discharges four Covid-19 patients